justification: Minimal modeling of Team B’s conservative, consensus-driven preferences; no mention of their valuing possession WRs or pocket QBs. The proposal mislabels Darian Anderson as a stable-floor WR (he’s Tier 5, outside, mid-variance). For a 1-7 Team A, giving up a Tier 2 QB and Tier 3 RB for a low-tier WR is incoherent with urgent win needs and A’s stated preferences. Rationale is brief and inaccurate.
